  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable Energy for the Displaced Communities - Mozambique</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of this project is to contribute to the inclusive economic and social development of the resettled internally displaced by Cyclone Idai in Mozambique through improved access to affordable energy and finance solutions. To achieve this objective, IOM will implement five components in an integrated manner to enhance synergies across sectors and optimize value for money. The project will develop a model for financial instruments targeting internally displaced persons to increase adoption of clean energy technologies with a focus on solar home systems and appliances for productive use. The approach will seek to create sustainable livelihood options that will not only improve beneficiaries&#xB4; living conditions but will also leverage and strengthen local markets.</narrative>
  </description>
